<HEADLINE> Canada's Building Permits Value Up in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Canada issued building permits
worth 2.9 billion dollars (2.0 billion US dollars) in November, up
8.4 percent from October, Statistics Canada reported today.
</P>
<P>
The figure represents the highest monthly level in more than
seven years, the statistics agency said.
</P>
<P>
The value of permits in the non-residential sector jumped 16.7
percent to 1.4 billion dollars. Non-residential permits went up in
nine of the first 11 months of 1997.
</P>
<P>
In the housing sector, more than 1.5 billion dollars worth of
building permits were issued, up 2.0 percent from October.
</P>
<P>
The residential sector did well throughout 1997, posting seven
monthly increases out of the first 11 months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
