<HEADLINE> Russia to Continue Investigating Basayev's Crime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prosecutor General Yury
Skuratov said Russia will continue to investigate the crimes of
Chechen field commander Shamil Basayev.
</P>
<P>
The prosecutor told a press conference Monday that the warrant
for Basayev's arrest issued by the Prosecutor General's Office in
1995 remains in effect.
</P>
<P>
The announcement came at a time when Basayev, the first deputy
minister of Chechnya, was asked to form a new cabinet by the Chechen
president who dismissed the current government on January 1.
</P>
<P>
Skuratov said Basayev is "a person charged with aggravated
crimes, including terrorism."
</P>
<P>
He said Basayev headed a Chechen unit that attacked the town of
Budyonnovsk in Stavropol territory in 1995. The attackers held
several hundred people hostage for several days at a hospital.
</P>
<P>
The investigation of the perpetrators of this crime has been
singled out as a separate case, which involves Commander of the
so-called Dedayev Army General Salman Raduyev and other Chechen
field commanders, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
