<HEADLINE> Four Killed in US Medical Helicopter Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 12 (Xinhua) -- A medical helicopter crashed
in a snowstorm on its way to a hospital after picking up an
injured skier near Salt Lake City today, killing all four people
aboard.
</P>
<P>
Searchers found the heavily damaged helicopter early this
morning in Little Cottonwood Canyon, about 30 kilometers southeast
of Salt Lake City, according to the Associated Press.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter, sent by the University of Utah Health Sciences
Center, took off from Snowbird Ski Resort Sunday night in a
snowstorm to rescue a skier injured in an avalanche.
</P>
<P>
Pilot Stan Berg, paramedic Tim Hynes, nurse Shane Carnahan and
the skier, David Anderson, were found killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
