<HEADLINE> World Bank, Vietnam Sign Agreement On Debt Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 12 (xinhua) -- An agreement on a 35 million
U.S. dollars International Development Association (IDA) credit
from the World Bank to Vietnam was signed here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam news agency reported that the IDA credit is
intended to finance a portion of the up-front cost of the Debt and
Debt-Service Reduction agreement (DDSR) signed in Paris on
December 16, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The loan will have a maturity of 40 years with a 10-year grace
period.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank has so far provided Vietnam with about 2 billion
U.S dollar in loans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
