<HEADLINE> URGENT: Iraq to Suspend Arms Inspection Team's Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Iraq has decided to stop any
arms inspections by the new U.N. team headed by an American, Scott
Ritter, which arrived here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In an announcement made by a government spokesman to the
official Iraq News Agency, Iraq said it will block the U.N. team
to conduct any activity in Iraq starting Tuesday until it is
recomposed through a balanced participation by permanent members
of the Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Ritter has been accused by Baghdad as an American spy.
</P>
<P>
The team, with nine Americans, five Britons, a Russian and an
Australian, has been criticized by Iraq as not balanced and
un-evenhanded in composition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
