<HEADLINE> Thai Government to Issue Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government Monday
decided to issue bonds from February 1 to raise money, in
particular foreign currencies at home and abroad, according to
local media reports.
</P>
<P>
The government bonds will be issued by the Government Savings
Bank.
</P>
<P>
The Thai government hopes to raise 500 million US dollars
through the bond issue.
</P>
<P>
At home, the Thai people will be encouraged to swap gold and
foreign currencies for bonds.
</P>
<P>
Last week the government adopted a number of measures to
tighten the control of foreign currency. The central bank will
monitor each foreign currency transaction by commercial banks, and
individuals buying foreign currency must provide air tickets or
visa.
</P>
<P>
Companies buying foreign currencies need to show necessary
documents, such as export bills.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Thai baht Monday sank to 56.40/56.60 per dollar
in the local market, and offshore it closed at 55.85/56.15 per
dollar.
</P>
<P>
The Stock Exchange of Thailand (SET) index also dropped by
10.50 points, to close at 339.17, a new low in 10 years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
