<HEADLINE> Ice Storm Hurts Canadian Insurers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The crippling ice storm that
swept central Canada may hurt the country's insurers harder than
last year's Winnipeg flood.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary estimates of damages from the storm in the Montreal
area alone have been placed at 500 million dollars (350 million
US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Damages in the national capital region and surrounding areas
have yet to be assessed, said reports today.
</P>
<P>
The Winnipeg flood may have caused more overall damages, but
they didn't hit insurers hard since flooding isn't covered in most
policies.
</P>
<P>
The latest ice storm will probably prompt a higher number of
claims, the reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
