<HEADLINE> German Shares Down in Reaction to Asian Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The German stocks market plunged
today in reaction to the Asian financial crisis, with the main DAX
index dropping by 149.66 points, or 3.53 percent, to close at
4,087.28 points in nervous floor trading.
</P>
<P>
The bank shares were hardest hit on the Frankfurt market with
investors fearing that Asian loans would turn bad.
</P>
<P>
On the foreign exchange market, the U.S. dollar remained almost
unchanged, fixed at 1.8158 German marks, compared to Friday's
1.8166 marks.
</P>
<P>
Some brokers in Frankfurt, encouraged by the positive signals
from South Korea and Indonesia, expected a quick recovery in the
Asian market, while others expected worsened prospects, citing the
collapse of Hong Kong's biggest investment bank Peregrine
Investment Holdings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
