<HEADLINE> Vietnam Readjusts Investment Priorities to Boost Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Investment priorities will be
given to the processing industry, the production of consumer goods,
the electronics industry, and to mechanical engineering,
Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Van Khai announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Khai made this announcement at a two-day national conference to
discuss the implementation of tasks set by the National Assembly
in 1998. The conference opened in Hanoi Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
Investment schemes should be readjusted with special attention
given to key projects, while avoiding unplanned investment, the prime
minister said.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should be made to boost services and develop infrastructure
facilities, Khai said.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed out the need to accomplish master plans for
developing infrastructure systems, key economic zones, and key
industries. He also emphasized the generation of new jobs programs.
</P>
<P>
He said that implementation of the tasks contained in the
resolution of the recent fourth plenum of the Vietnamese Communist
Party Central Committee, and the resolution of the 10th National
Assembly, must ensure a sustainable and high pace of growth for
the economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
