<HEADLINE> Germans Spend 4.5 Bln Marks Each Year Keeping Pets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Germans are spending 4.5 billion
marks (2.5 billion U.S. dollars) each year in keeping their pets,
3.2 billion marks (1.8 billion dollars) of the sum for pet food
alone, the association of German pet stores reported today in
Berlin.
</P>
<P>
According to the association, cats are the most favorite pets
kept by Germans, where there are 6.2 million. Dogs come next,
totaling 5.1 million.
</P>
<P>
About 12.3 million of German households, or 34 percent, are
keeping 23.6 million pets excluding aquarium fish, the association
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
