famous Masai Mara National Reserve may be forced to close down
their business if the current heavy rains continue pounding the
area.
</P>
<P>
Lorries and trucks transporting foodstuff, beverages and fuel
have been stuck along the muddy Narok-Masai Mara road for several
days while efforts to mobilize heavy duty tractors to tow them
out have been fruitless.
</P>
<P>
The hotels and lodges are experiencing problems in organizing
game drives as the reserve is water-logged, the report added.
