<HEADLINE> Silicon Valley Sustains Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Silicon Valley, a
technology-driven growth area in the western United States, has
sustained its boom especially in the manufacturing sector.
</P>
<P>
The region added 53,000 jobs in 1997 and showed strength in the
production of software and other information technology products,
the New York Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
Citing a survey report on the region's economic and social
health by corporate and civic organizations, the paper said
Silicon Valley now generates 40 percent of California's exports,
with its population accounting only for 10 percent of the state's
total.
</P>
<P>
The Valley surpassed Detroit as the country's leading exporter
in 1996, the study found.
</P>
<P>
Silicon Valley, originally limited to Santa Clara County on the
southwest side of the San Francisco Bay, now is expanded to an
area of 1,500 square miles with a population of 2.3 million.
</P>
