<HEADLINE> IFC Launches Japanese Yen Dual Currency Global Notes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) today announced the launching of a Japanese Yen
5 billion dual currency note issue under its Global Medium-Term
Note program.
</P>
<P>
The dual currency note issue which consists of Yen coupon and
U.S. dollar principal redemption is targeted at the Japanese
retail market.
</P>
<P>
The 3-year fixed-rate notes carry a semi-annual coupon of 4.05
percent per annum and were issued on a par.
</P>
<P>
The sole lead manager of the issue is Toronto Dominion
Securities.
</P>
<P>
The latest transaction has brought IFC's market borrowing for
the fiscal year 1998 to about 1,910 million U.S. dollars
equivalent. IFC's Market Borrowing started on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
IFC is a member of the World Bank Group and is regarded as the
largest multilateral source of financing for private sector
projects in developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
