<HEADLINE> China Construction Bank Profitable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank
(CCB), one of the country's big four, had 1.51 billion yuan (about
180 million US dollars) in profits in 1997, according to bank
statistics.
</P>
<P>
This is the first real profit for the bank, which used to
extend fixed asset loans, since 1993, its president, Wang Qishan,
told an annual meeting today.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that eliminating losses and making a profit was
encouraging. Statistics show a growth in CCB's deposits of 152
billion yuan to 1.25 trillion yuan at the end of last year. The
value of the bank's loans grew 116.4 billion yuan to more than
1.02 trillion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The bank did 50.3 billion US dollars in foreign trade
settlements last year, up 44 percent. It also issued 20.7 million
credit cards, and did 374.2 billion yuan in credit card business.
</P>
<P>
Wang said his bank successfully maintained its leading position
in financing policy-oriented housing last year, with 15 billion
yuan in housing loans, more than 70 percent of the market share.
</P>
<P>
It also made substantial progress in internal restructuring and
personnel reforms, with 150 county-level branches with poor
business records being closed or downgraded, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
