<HEADLINE> New Leaders of HKYIC Inaugurate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Young
Industrialists Council (HKYIC) held an inauguration ceremony here
Tuesday for the new members of its Executive Committee.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region of China, presented certificates to the new
members of the committee, with Charles Yeung as the president.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the inauguration ceremony, Yeung said that the HKYIC
had made great achievements in the past year, during which Hong
Kong experienced the historical moment of returning to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
In the new year, the HKYIC will make efforts to promote Hong
Kong's high value-added industry as pointed out by the chief
executive in his Policy Address made in October last year, Yeung
said.
</P>
<P>
The HKYIC, established in 1992 as a non-profit-making
organization, comprises the winners of the "Young Industrialist
Award" each year and a group of young and successful entrepreneurs
in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Since its founding, HKYIC aims at fostering industrial and
economic development in Hong Kong and inland of China, and has
promoted opportunities for economic co-operation between China and
 other countries.
</P>
<P>
Besides, HKYIC has encouraged idea exchange between Hong Kong
industrialists and government officials, as well as leaders of
social organizations of the inland of China.
</P>
<P>
In order to meet the escalating demand for qualified staff,
HKYIC has run training courses to nurture professionals.
</P>
<P>
Most of the HKYIC members have played pioneering roles in
investing in the inland of China by establishing factories. They
currently employ more than 360,000 work force in the inland and
the annual trading turnover amounts to 55.7 billion HK dollars
(7.14 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Some of the HKYIC members have been elected to the Executive
Council of the SAR government and the Provisional Legislative
Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
