<HEADLINE> Nanjing Starts Building Second Yangtze River Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Work began today on Nanjing's
Beicha Bridge, the second highway bridge across the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The bridge is 11 km downstream from the present bridge and
connects with the third largest island on the Yangtze. It consists
of the Nancha and Beicha bridges and a 16-km-long road and will
cost 3.2 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Beicha Bridge is scheduled for completion by December 31,
in the year 2000. It is a 2,212-meter pre-stressed concrete
structure, 32 meters wide.
</P>
<P>
Work on the Nancha began on October 6. The new bridge is
expected to relieve the traffic jams on the Nanjing Bridge and
help the economy of Jiangsu and neighboring provinces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
