<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Procuratorates in Shenzhen,
China's first special economic zone, in Guangdong Province,
arrested 132 officials last year for involvement in economic
crimes like corruption and bribery.
</P>
<P>
According to a city conference of procuratorates that opened
here today, procurators confiscated a total of 57.2 million yuan
in bribery from the offenders.
</P>
