<HEADLINE> HK External Trade Up in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's re-exports
increased by 6.3 percent to hit 106.7 billion HK dollars (13.7
billion U.S. dollars) in November 1997 over a year earlier, the
Census and Statistics Department announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The value of domestic exports, at 18 billion HK dollars (2.3
billion U.S. dollars), was little changed while imports increased
by a moderate 1.5 percent to 133 billion HK dollars (17.1 billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Comparing the first 11 months of 1997 with the same period of
1996, the value of re-exports increased by 4.7 percent to 1,138.8
billion HK dollars (146 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, the value of domestic exports, totaling 192.7 billion
HK dollars (24.7 billion U.S. dollars) in the period, decreased by
0.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The value of imports in the 11 months, at 1,477.3 billion HK
dollars (189.4 billion U.S. dollars), rose by 5.2 percent from the
same period of the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
