<HEADLINE> Braaten Claims Surprise World Cup Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Norwegian Kenneth Braaten, who
joined the Nordic combined World Cup circuit in late December,
claimed a surprise victory in Ramsau, Austria on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland's Marco Zarucchi and Urs Kunz were second and
third, 4.2 and 10.1 seconds behind, in an event which had
originally been scheduled for Harrachov in the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
Braaten, whose victory was Norway's 50th in World Cup Nordic
combined competitions, was ninth after the ski-jumping leg before
recording the sixth-best cross-country time.
</P>
<P>
Second place gave Zarucchi his best career result while Kunz
won the cross-country leg to improve on a 16th place after the
jumping.
</P>
<P>
Alexei Fadeev, who became the first Russian to win a Nordic
combined ski jumping leg, was a poor 29th in cross-country for
overall fifth place.
</P>
<P>
Norway's Bjarte Engen Vik continues to head the overall
standings on 820 points despite a disappointing 41st place on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Austria's Mario Stecher is second on 730 points and Finland's
Hannu Manninen third on 622.
</P>
<P>
The Nordic combined World cup continues with a competition in
Chaux-Neuve, France, on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980113.0102 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Refuses to Impose Import Surtax </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Finance Secretary
Roberto de Ocampo said Tuesday that his department has turned down
a proposal to impose a temporary surcharge tax on all imports that
compete with locally produced goods.
</P>
<P>
"While we agree that domestic manufacturing firms will face a
tough test this year due to higher interest rates, higher cost of
imported inputs and low consumer confidence, we believe that the
proposal is not the remedy to these problems," de Ocampo said.
</P>
<P>
The drastic proposal was raised last week by the Federation of
Philippine Industries Inc. on the grounds that it can partially
offset the projected huge fiscal deficit of the government,
prevent massive layoffs and conserve foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
The federation warned that massive layoffs might occur
beginning this month in the event the current volatility in the
foreign exchange market persisted and interest rates showed no
signs of easing.
</P>
<P>
Describing the proposal as "counter-productive", de Ocampo said
it will affect the competitiveness of business since the imported
inputs will cost more due to the additional tariff.
</P>
<P>
The proposal has an element of protectionism which contradicts
both the government's policy on trade liberalization and the
country's commitment to the World Trade Organization (WTO), he
said.
</P>
<P>
According to de Ocampo, the Philippines has committed to the
WTO not to discriminate imported goods against domestic goods
through internal revenue taxes.
</P>
<P>
De Ocampo also doubted the proposal will increase the revenues
of the government since it will not necessarily increase
collections of the Bureau of Customs.
</P>
<P>
Instead, he said, a surtax will lower imports and might be an
incentive to smuggle or import through the duty-free shops.
</P>
<P>
A surtax is unnecessary as the exchange rate itself regulates
trade and that imports naturally decline if the exchange rate
depreciates, de Ocampo said.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine peso, a victim of the Asian financial crisis,
has so far lost more than 65 percent in its value against the U.S.
dollar since its de facto devaluation in July 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980113.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Donations Continue To Come To Aid Of Northern Chinese Disaster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Donations continue to
arrive in Zhangjiakou in north China's Hebei Province from other
parts of the country, after the earthquake measuring 6.2 on the
Richter scale hit it last Saturday at 11:50 am (Beijing Time).
</P>
<P>
By this morning, the area had received 13.4 million yuan relief
funds, 47,000 items of cotton-padded clothing, 73,000
cotton-padded quilts, 309,000 kg of fast food, and large
quantities rice, flour, tents, wood, coal, and ovens.
</P>
<P>
The goods came mainly from the armed forces, nearby provinces
and cities, and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, the earthquake has killed 47
people and seriously injured over 250, and damaged or destroyed
over 70,000 houses in Zhangbei and Shangyi counties.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to rescue efforts, there have been no deaths resulting
from the sub-zero temperatures in the area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
