<HEADLINE> China Makes International Appeal For Earthquake Assistance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The Red Cross Society of China
(RCSC) has appealed to the international community for ten million
yuan (about 1.2 million US dollars) in aid to assist the area of
Hebei Province that was hit by Saturday's earthquake.
</P>
<P>
The International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent
Societies has informed member societies all over the world about
the conditions and allocated 75,000 Swiss francs for disaster
relief, the RCSC said today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 3,400 blankets donated by Japan's Red Cross Society
arrived in Beijing tonight, and the Japanese government says it
will provide 300,000 US dollars worth of tents, blankets and
generators.
</P>
<P>
Enkas P.H. Chau and Wilson M.F. Wong of the Hong Kong Red Cross
came to Beijing today to discuss the use of six million yuan in
relief funds, which was provided by the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
The RCSC has provided 500 quilts and 5,000 items of winter
clothing, as well as tents, food, medicines, and relief funds that
were raised by its branches across the country.
</P>
<P>
RCSC officers say they expect more donation in coming days.
</P>
