<HEADLINE> Beijing's First Heavy Snow This Winter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Heavy snowfall in Beijing
caused a few traffic accidents in the downtown area an hour after
it began at 9 a.m. today, and many say they've not seen anything
like it for years.
</P>
<P>
But, the snow will benefit crops, and help remove some of the
grime in the air. There will be fairly clean and humid air
conditions in Beijing, meteorologist Wang Guitian says.
</P>
<P>
A large number of children have been going for medical help,
according to a doctor at Beijing Children's Hospital, where there
were 4,000 every day recently, most of them suffering from
respiratory tract infections.
</P>
<P>
The snow will effectively check the further spread of the flu,
says a medical worker at Beijing Medical University.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to last for two or three days and might be
heavier this evening, according to the Beijing Meteorology
Bureau. 
</P>
