<HEADLINE> Business Receipts Up for Most of HK's Service Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Business receipts in most of
Hong Kong service industries showed remarkable year-on-year
increases in the third quarter of 1997, the Census and Statistics
Department revealed Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The value of business receipts in the financing (except
banking) industry registered the fastest growth -- 66 percent.
This was followed by the communications industry which recorded a
26 percent increase in business receipts, provisional figures from
the department showed.
</P>
<P>
The robust increase in the financing (except banking) industry
was due to significantly higher stock market turnover and strong
performance of the capital market in the third quarter. Reflecting
this, within the industry, the financial markets and fund
management sector recorded triple-digit growth of 131 percent in
business receipts.
</P>
<P>
The surge in business receipts in the communications industry
was attributable to the rapid expansion of the telecommunications
industry.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, considerable increases in business receipts were
also registered in the real estate, business services, insurance
and banking industries.
</P>
<P>
But business receipts in the tourism, convention and exhibition
services domain and the hotels industry dropped by 21 percent and
15 percent, respectively, in the quarter, when there was a steep
decline in the number of tourist arrivals partly due to the
regional currency turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is a services-dominated economy with the services
industry contributing 84 percent of its gross domestic product.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
