workers through commercial airline flights, they may be compelled
to ask the Philippine Air Force to dispatch a C-130 cargo plane to
Seoul to fetch the workers.
</P>
<P>
Of the 3,000 displaced Filipino workers in South Korea, the
official said, 93 have already returned to the Philippines on
their own account and expenses.
</P>
<P>
He added that they expect more of the laid off Filipino workers
who have money of their own to finance their airfare back to
Manila.
</P>
<P>
Reports said many of the Filipino workers who lost jobs are
unskilled labor and are undocumented who came to Korea as
tourists.
</P>
<P>
The official said the Philippine government, through the
Department of Labor and Employment, will shortly set into motion a
program designed to create jobs and absorb the displaced Filipino
workers from their overseas jobs.  
