<HEADLINE> 700 Kilos of Explosives Found in West Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January 13 (Xinhua) -- A total of 700 kilograms of
explosives were found and four activists arrested in a raid by the
Palestinian security forces on a Hamas bomb factory in the West
Bank town of Nablus Monday night, local media reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The raid was conducted with the cooperation of the Israeli army
intelligence, which provided the Palestinian side with detailed
activities of the factory, Palestinian police sources were quoted
as saying.
</P>
<P>
During the raid, the explosives were found in the factory in a
residential building in Nablus, which was suspected for making
bombs and other explosive devices.
</P>
<P>
Four Hamas (Islamic Resistance Movement) activists who were
seen going in and out of the bomb factory were arrested in their
homes in Nablus.
</P>
<P>
During the last few days, the Israeli security forces both in
Israel and the West Bank areas were ordered to be on high alert
against terrorist attacks by the Islamic militants.
</P>
<P>
In Israel, roadblocks have been set up at the entrances to the
cities and more police deployed in public places.
</P>
<P>
The Central Command of the Israeli Defense Forces (IDF) Monday
ordered all settlers in the West Bank to beef up security in their
settlements.
</P>
<P>
The security cooperation between Israelis and Palestinians has
been strengthened, and a hot-line was set up between the
security chiefs of the two sides during U.S. peace envoy Dennis
Ross's visit to the region last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
