<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Breakthrough Progress Urged in SOE Reform This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Great efforts should be made to
achieve breakthrough progress in reforming China's state-owned
enterprises this year, according to a People's Daily commentary
today.
</P>
<P>
The annual central economic conference held in Beijing by the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the
State Council from December 9-11 set six major tasks for this
year's economic work.
</P>
<P>
Among the six major tasks, completing the crucial stage of
restructuring state-owned enterprises and achieving breakthrough
progress in this regard have been considered essential to making
the whole year's work a success.
</P>
<P>
It fully demonstrates that the CPC Central Committee and the
State Council have placed advancement of reform in state-owned
enterprises at a very obvious position, said the commentary.
</P>
<P>
While calling for a thorough understanding of existing
problems, the commentary also said that it is necessary to be
confident and overcome the feeling of shrinking from the
difficulty.
</P>
<P>
Stepping up reforms in state-owned enterprises is a crucial
battle because more deep-rooted contradictions of state
enterprises, such as heavy debts and rising redundant workers,
will be fully revealed and cannot be avoided. This makes it an
urgent, as well as difficult, task to improve efficiency by laying
off workers and providing new jobs for them, said the commentary.
</P>
<P>
"It is necessary to forge ahead amid difficulties, and uphold
the confidence of achieving a success at the crucial stage of
restructuring the state-owned enterprises," the commentary stated.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said it is imperative to have a clear
understanding of the favorable situations for furthering reform of
state-owned enterprises, which will serve as a powerful supporting
force to make the crucial stage work of restructuring the
state-owned enterprises a success.
</P>
<P>
Three favorable conditions include:
</P>
<P>
-- Concrete measures worked out by the CPC Central Committee
and the State Council governing implementation of reform of
state-owned enterprises;
</P>
<P>
-- Greater support for restructuring state enterprises in
China's macro-policies;
</P>
<P>
-- Many precious experiences accumulated for solving problems
in state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The commentary added that it would be an inevitable outcome to
achieve a breakthrough in restructuring state enterprises, the key
to reforming the current entire economic system, as long as the
strategic goals set by the 15th CPC National Congress are pursued
with confidence and unswerving efforts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
