<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets US Governor of Minnesota </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
met with Arne Carlson, governor of the US state of Minnesota, and
his party here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China is the largest developing country while the
US is the largest developed country and the expansion of the
cooperation between the two nations not only is in line with the
fundamental interests of the two peoples, but also serves the
global peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
China is ready to increase exchange and collaboration with the
US states in every area, Li told the visitors.
</P>
<P>
Carlson said that the people of Minnesota have a "strong
feeling" towards the Chinese people. More than 200 firms
from Minnesota are now doing business in China and quite a number
of enterprises are planning to seek economic and trade
opportunities in the country, he added.
</P>
<P>
The governor said that his state hopes to enhance cooperation
with the Chinese side in the fields of economy, education and
aviation.
</P>
<P>
