<HEADLINE> Coffee Export Down in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Coffee export in Uganda
dropped to 241,147 bags (60 kg per bag) in December 1997,
compared with 514,394 bags in the same month the previous year,
Uganda Coffee Development Authority (UCDA) said.
</P>
<P>
The value of coffee export also went down from 35.8 million
U.S. Dollars in December 1996 to 21.6 million Dollars last
December, said the UCDA monthly report.
</P>
<P>
But still, the performance last December is an improvement as
against that of last November which witnessed an export of
179,604 bags and 16.07 million Dollars in earning, the report
noted.
</P>
<P>
UCDA attributed the slight improvement to the increase of
world coffee prices caused in part by the rise in demand and
coffee exporters from 26 in November to 30 in December 1997.
</P>
<P>
The report blamed the reduction in coffee export on heavy
rains which had delayed the collecting of coffee beans and
hindered the drying.
</P>
<P>
Coffee is the most important export item in Uganda which
accounts for 65 percent of country's foreign exchange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
