<HEADLINE> South Korea's Hyundai Launches New Car in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 13 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's Hyundai Motor
Company Tuesday launched its new car model "Santro" in India.
</P>
<P>
The 1000 cc Santro, an upgraded version of "Atos" model, will
hit the roads by October 1998, said Mong Gyu Chung, chairman of
the company here.
</P>
<P>
Hyundai expected to produce 3,000 cars per month to start with.
</P>
