Production will increase to 10,000 cars per month by the end of
1999. Some Santro cars produced in India would be exported to the
neighboring countries, said B. V. R. Subbu, director of sales and
marketing of Hyundai Motor India.
</P>
<P>
Hyundai has already invested 22,000 million rupees (602.74
million US dollars) in its 100 percent Indian subsidiary and would
be investing another 10,000 rupees (270.27 million dollars) before
the turn of the century.
</P>
<P>
The recent crisis in South Korea and depreciation of its
currency would not affect Hyundai's investment plans for India,
Mong Gyu Chung said.  
