<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market
Tuesday regained some of Monday's sharp losses as buyers cheered
at the strength of better Asian markets and the overnight Wall
Street rise.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index rose 22.9 points to 2565.3 with almost
all the rise attributable to industrial stocks.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index improved 49.5 points to 4449.0, with
News Corp particularly strong.
</P>
<P>
Ordinary shares in Rupert Murdoch's global company jumped 30.8
cents and the preferred shares rose 24.5 cents as the market
welcomed the continuing strength of the film Titanic, distributed
by 20th Century Fox.
</P>
<P>
Telstra's installment receipts also recovered from Monday's
steep fall to improve five cents. Turnover was 14.8 million
shares.
</P>
<P>
Banking stocks rose, with Westpac achieving the best gain of 16
cents with 3.4 million shares turned over. National Australia Bank
improved 17.5 cents, ANZ added two and Commonwealth Bank rose four
cents.
</P>
<P>
Resources failed to improve much as buyers remained wary of a
gloomy outlook for commodities. The all resources index rose just
0.3 points to 1055.2.
</P>
<P>
Gold stocks improved, with the index up 9.5 points to 961.1 as
bullion fell 0.25 per ounce to 277.65 US dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 264.9 million shares at a value of 760.06
million Australian dollars (486.43 million US dollars) with falls
bettering rises 547 to 50. 
</P>
