<HEADLINE> Two Lots Sold at Hong Kong's Land Auction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The government of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) Tuesday sold two lots for
private residential and non-industrial purposes at a public
auction in the Concert Hall of the Hong Kong Cultural Center.
</P>
<P>
The two government lots are worth a total of 283 million Hong
Kong dollars (36.38 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The first lot, located at Tsing Sin Street, Tuen Mun, covers
3,875 square meters. It was bought by Brighwing Development
Limited for 250 million Hong Kong dollars (32.13 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The lot is designated for non-industrial purposes, excluding
warehouses, gas stations, hotels and service apartments.
</P>
<P>
The second lot, at Tong Yan San Tsuen, Yuen Long, with an area
of 2,042 square meters, was sold to Lead Fortune Development
Limited for 33 million Hong Kong dollars (4.24 million U.S.
dollars), with bidding opened at 20 million Hong Kong dollars
(2.57 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The lot is intended for private residential purposes excluding
service apartments. The developer has to complete a gross floor
area of not less than 1,200 square meters on or before March 21,
2001.
</P>
<P>
This was the sixth land auction conducted by the Lands
Department of the SAR government since handover on July 1 last
year.  
