<HEADLINE> Beninese President Satisfied With Benin-China Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Beninese President Mathieu
Kerekou said he is satisfied with the relations between Benin
and China, according to report from Beninese capital Porto
Novo Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Kerekou, who is to visit China in the near future, made the
remarks while meeting Chinese Ambassador to Benin Duan Chunlai.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Kerekou said, he will hold talks with Chinese
President Jiang Zemin on furthering bilateral cooperation as well
as international and regional issues.
</P>
<P>
The Beninese government will maintain its one-China policy and
will not have official relationship with Taiwan, the president
said.
</P>
<P>
It will be Kerekou's third China visit after those he made in
1976 and 1986, the report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
