<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poll Unbeatable in Women's 200m Freestyle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champion Claudia Poll led
all the way to win the women's 200m freestyle final at the world
swimming championships here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Costa Rican timed one minute and 58.90 seconds,
beating second-place finisher Martina Moravcova of Slovakia by
0.31 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Australian Julia Greville got the bronze medal in a time of
1:59.92.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Taipei's Tsai Shu-min missed the medal podium by
finishing fourth in 1:59.93.
</P>
<P>
Poll was the 200m and 400m freestyle winner at the Pan Pacific
championships last year.
</P>
<P>
Moravcova was the silver medalist over 100m at the 1997
European championships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
