<HEADLINE> East China City Passes Foreign Investment Regulations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Weihai, a city in east China's
Shandong Province, has enhanced protection of foreign investors'
interests by releasing four detailed regulations on
administration, dispute settlement, favorable policies and fees of
foreign investment in the city.
</P>
<P>
One of the regulations sets specific standards for the
establishment of foreign-funded enterprises as well as changes,
termination, operation management, human resources management, and
accounting and statistical systems.
</P>
<P>
Another regulation elaborates the conditions, proceedings,
settlement requirements and government employee disciplines of
handling complaints by foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
The third involved favorable policies for foreign-funded
processing enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The fourth stipulates strict supervision over relevant
authorities levying fees on foreign-funded companies. According to
the regulation, foreign-funded companies have the right to refuse
levies that are not stipulated in relevant laws and to make
complaints to local price supervision authorities. The price
authorities will investigate the complaints and hand out
punishment according to the law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
