<HEADLINE> Russian Sedakova Wins Synchrozined Swimming Solo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Russian Olga Sedakova put up a
nearly perfect performance to take the synchronized swimming solo
final at the world swimming championships here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It was the fourth gold medal that Russia won in Perth.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old Russian got a total of 99.304 points, beating
Virginie Dedieu by 1.150 points into second place and denying her
a chance to win France first gold medal at the championships.
</P>
<P>
Sedakova registered two perfect 10s for technical merit with
the other three judges all scoring 9.9.
</P>
<P>
The Russian won three 10s and two 9.9s for artistic impression.
</P>
<P>
Japanese Miya Tachibana picked the bronze medal with 95.790
points.
</P>
<P>
China's Li Min finished seventh in the final, the best-ever
performance by Chinese in world championship synchronized swimming
solo event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
