<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Exports Rice for First Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 13 (Xinhua)-- Vietnam for the first time ever
exported rice produced in the northern provinces in 1997.
</P>
<P>
By the end of December last year, the Northern Food Corporation
exported 102,000 tonnes of rice, according to local press reports.
</P>
<P>
Being labelled a "narrow but over-populated" land, the northern
provinces in the past were barely self-sufficient in food.
</P>
<P>
Each year, the north had to import up to one million tonnes of
paddy equivalent to 500,000 tonnes of rice from the Mekong delta,
Vietnam's largest "rice basket".
</P>
<P>
With the agricultural economy restructured, the northern
provinces are heading towards export-oriented production. 
</P>
</TEXT>
