<HEADLINE> Sautin Beats Zhou Sound and Flat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Olympic platform diving champion
Dmitri Sautin beat Chinese Zhou Yilin convincingly as he got an
outstanding total of 746.79 points at the men's 3m springboard
final at the world swimming championships here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian star scored over 93 points apiece in his fourth and
fifth dives, running away from the rest of the field. It was the
fifth gold medal won by Russia in the championships.
</P>
<P>
Zhou, currently China's best springboard diver, scored 694.92
points for the silver medal, with Russian Vassiliy Lisovskiy
getting the bronze in 651.60.
</P>
<P>
The gap of 51.87 was the biggest ever between Sautin and Zhou
and it signaled China had lost its dominance over the men's
springboard event.
</P>
<P>
Zhou, who last year won six international springboard titles in
absence of Sautin, had lost both of his two encounters with the
Russian.
</P>
<P>
Sautin edged Zhou by 6.9 points in the U.S. Grand Prix last May
and won over the Chinese again by a thin margin of 0.96 points in
the World Cup last October.
</P>
<P>
"Sautin dived far better than me," said Zhou. "He has very
strong mentality and consistency." 
</P>
</TEXT>
