<HEADLINE> German Inflation at 1.8 Percent in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, Jnauary 13 (Xinhua) -- Germany's inflation for the year
1997 rose to 1.8 percent, up 0.3 percent from the level a year
earlier, the Federal Statistics Office reported Tuesday in
Wiesbaden.
</P>
<P>
Last August saw the inflation rate on an annual base arriving
at the peak of 2.1 percent, the office said, after which inflation
slowed down.
</P>
<P>
Inflation in eastern area of Germany stood at 2.1 percent last
year, due to higher food and housing prices, while that in the
western Germany was 1.8 percent. 
</P>
