<HEADLINE> Official: Quake Victims Protected from Cold, Hunger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 13 (Xinhua) -- People in Zhangjiakou
received disaster relief goods and funds soon after a strong quake
jolted the area on Jan. 10.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Wan Fang, head of the Hebei Provincial
Anti-Quake and Disaster Relief Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
He said, though the temperature of quake-hit areas at night
reached 20 degrees below zero Centigrade, a large number of
cotton-padded overcoats, quilts and food rushed to the area have
solved the basic needs of people in the quake-damaged areas.
</P>
<P>
Wan said the provincial government held four meetings in a day
after the quake measuring 6.2 on the Richter scale hit the area at
noon on Saturday. Ten trucks loaded with overcoats, quilts, tents
and food arrived at the quake-hit areas that evening.
</P>
<P>
Wan added that 13 medical teams rushed to the area soon after
the quake.
</P>
<P>
By Jan. 12 the quake-hit area had received 13.4 million yuan in
relief funds, 47,000 cotton-padded coats, 73,000 quilts, 618,000
kilograms of fast food, and large amount of heating materials and
cooking facilities.
</P>
<P>
Though the tents and make-shift shelters are not as warm as
ordinary houses, he said, people there have enough fuel to keep
the temporary living places safe from the cold.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, Xinhua reporters in Zhangbei said
People's Liberation Army troops and rescue workers are speeding up
the installation of tents and make-shift shelters.
</P>
<P>
When they toured several villages in Zhangbei Monday night, the
two reporters heard snoring sounds coming from the make-shift
shelters.
</P>
<P>
In a tent hospital in Dahe Township, a woman gave birth to a
baby girl just one day after the quake. Another pregnant woman
approaching her expected date of childbirth is awaiting the birth
of her baby at the hospital bed.
</P>
<P>
Just two weeks before China's lunar calendar new year,
8-year-old Zhao Xiuping told Xinhua that she was rescued from her
collapsed house one day after the shock. Her wish is to have a
pair of new shoes for the coming of Spring Festival, China's most
important holiday celebration.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
