<HEADLINE> 300,000 People Need Food Aid in S. Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 13 (Xinhua) -- More than 300,000 people in
Masvingo province in southern Zimbabwe are desperate for food aid
and had by last Friday registered for help with their respective
district administrators.
</P>
<P>
Alphonse Chikurira, Provincial Administrator for Masvingo,
said on Monday 301,000 people had applied for relief food under
the government's grain loan scheme.
</P>
<P>
This means one in every four people in this drought-prone
province with 1.2 million population, is now in a dire situation,
he noted.
</P>
<P>
According to Chikurira, district administrators in the
southeastern province were still processing more applications.
</P>
<P>
The number of those in need of relief food is expected to rise
to 350,000 soon due to the continued decline in food reserves in
the province.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, more people countrywide are expected to apply for
food aid this year because of the predicted drought.
</P>
<P>
But the government has assured the nation that nobody will die
from hunger as it had enough maize. 
</P>
</TEXT>
