<HEADLINE> Diarrhea Kills Four in Bengkulu, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Diarrhea has been plaguing
several villages in South Bengkulu province, Indonesia, killing
four people who failed to get medical care promptly enough, Antara
News Agency Tuesday quoted a local health official as saying.
</P>
<P>
Head of the South Bengkulu Health Department Yusdi Zahrias said
that 76 others have suffered but so far survived the diarrhea
outbreak, which broke out last week, after receiving immediate
medical help.
</P>
<P>
He said the epidemic was spreading as local people consumed
water from a polluted river and wells.
</P>
<P>
To prevent more victims, Zahrias said his office has set up
several health posts to curb the epidemic, involving ten
physicians in the effort.  
</P>
</TEXT>
