<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets U.S. Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
met here today with a U.S. delegation from Minnesota state led by
its governor, Arne Carlson.
</P>
<P>
Jiang extended a warm welcome to the delegation, saying that
China and Minnesota have a history of long-term friendship.
</P>
<P>
During recent years Minnesota has actively carried out economic
and trade cooperation with China and, so far, many corporations of
the state have opened their business here, he said.
</P>
<P>
The president pointed out that the economies of China and the
United States are highly complementary, and his U.S. visit last
fall created new opportunities for bilateral economic and trade
cooperation while stimulating steady progress in overall bilateral
ties.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Minnesota would expand its
cooperation with the central and western regions of China to
contribute more to the development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Carlson said that Minnesota has maintained long-term friendly
cooperation with China. The state is willing to give full play to
its advantages in such sectors as agriculture, commerce and
electronics, and to further increase their cooperation with China
in these fields.
</P>
<P>
The delegation arrived in Beijing Sunday at the invitation of
the China Council for the Promotion of International
Trade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
