<HEADLINE> Finding Jobs For Unemployed People In Northeast China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Dalian, a port city in northeast
China's Liaoning Province, managed to find work for 100,000
laid-off workers by improving its employment market last year.
</P>
<P>
The city has worked in the process to hold the unemployment
rate for about a million workers to below 3 percent.
</P>
<P>
At the beginning of last year, the city's labor department
began separating laid-off workers into five groups to help
them. It found jobs for 20,000 workers, got 30,000 people to
change their work through job training courses, and helped the
rest find new jobs through an improved labor market system.
</P>
<P>
The local government also set up an insurance network that
covers pensions, unemployment benefits, medicare, maternity leave,
and on the job injuries.  
</P>
