east of Zhangjiakou Prefecture in north China's Hebei province to
Beijing posed difficulties to transport of disaster relief
materials to Zhangbei and Shangyi counties, the hardest-hit areas
by the quake. In addition, people in the quake-hit areas are
expected to have more problems recovering from the quake measuring
6.2 on the Richter scale which killed 47 people and injured more
than 10,000. (China-Zhangbei-Quake Area)
