<HEADLINE> Inland Province to Explore New Overseas Markets: Governor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Land-locked Shanxi Province in
north China will concentrate itself on exploring markets in
Latin America, India, Russia, the Middle East, Africa and
Australia in the next few years.
</P>
<P>
Governor Xue Rongzhe told the Beijing-based International
Business Daily that the province will focus on the Latin American
market in 1998. The province expects to set up a trade center in
Brazil and agricultural joint ventures in Argentina this year.
</P>
<P>
Xue said this is part of Shanxi's long-term strategy of
marketing its principal products abroad.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the next three-to-five years the province will
concentrate on developing quality products that will bring at
least 10 million U.S. dollars in export revenue annually.
</P>
<P>
The quality products include such items as pitch coke,
magnesium, steel pipes, horticultural and gardening products, and
frozen rabbit meat.
</P>
<P>
The province will form 10 large-scale business groups
spearheaded by manufacturers of the quality products. The groups
will include the Taiyuan Steel Company, Fenjiu Liquor, Shanxi
Coke, Yungang Cement and Green Food.
</P>
<P>
It will also build four computerized information networks
hooked to the Internet throughout the province.
</P>
<P>
The province will train 100 senior business executives in
international marketing, 1,000 mid-level international marketing
managers and 10,000 salespersons who are familiar with the
international market.
</P>
<P>
Xue said that the province will increase its exposure to
international markets to increase the competitiveness of local
enterprises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
