<HEADLINE> Iran Condemns Terrorist Actions in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Ministry has
condemned terrorist activities against innocent people in
Pakistan, Tehran radio reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi Monday termed
recent criminal acts of terrorists against Shiite Muslims in
Pakistan during the holy fasting month of Ramadan as "savage."
</P>
<P>
Media reports said that at least 22 people were killed Sunday
when unidentified attackers opened fire on a crowd at a Shia
Muslim religious ceremony in the Pakistani city of Lahore.
</P>
<P>
The massacre triggered a new wave of demonstration in
Pakistan, in which the demonstrators urged the Pakistani
government to take more serious measures against terrorist
activities in the country.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi said that the attack on the defenseless civilians at
the time of their performance of religious ceremonies is a clear
demonstration of enmity with Islam.
</P>
<P>
He called on the Pakistani government to continue its campaign
against terrorist groups in the country and try to use all means
possible within its power to fully quell the inhuman terrorist
elements "so that Pakistani community could once more live under
the aegis of security, peace and tranquility." 
