<HEADLINE> Four Tanzanians Die After Eating Poisonous Turtle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Four residents in the
Coast Region of Tanzania have lost their lives after eating the
meat of a poisonous turtle, press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Another 21 people who also ate the meat last week have been
discharged from hospital after recovery, Shihata reported.
</P>
<P>
"The situation is now calm," the news agency quoted Coast
Region Acting Police Commander Philip Mgandila as saying.
</P>
<P>
The police commander has appealed to local residents to give
up the habit of eating turtle meat. 
</P>
