Williams upset world number one Swiss Martina Hingis in the second
round of the Sydney international tennis tournament on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Playing under scortching sun and drenching humidity, the two
17-year-olds slogged out a three-set marathon battle for two and a
half hours on Center Court as both required treatment for cramps.
</P>
<P>
Williams, seeded 21st, eventually triumphed 3-6, 6-4, 7-5 over
Hingis, avenging her straight-set defeat last September in the
U.S. Open final against the Swiss teenager.
</P>
