second set and required a medical timeout and treatment on court
at 1-1 in the third set.
</P>
<P>
But Hingis failed to capitalize on the injury and took her
medical timeout to deal with cramps at 5-5 before Williams swept
the final two games, winning both at love.
</P>
<P>
Last January, Hingis won the Sydney tournament and then the
Australian Open in Melbourne before she overtook Germany's Steffi
Graf as world number one in March.
</P>
<P>
Williams will play either Magdalena Maleeva of Bulgaria or
fellow American Chanda Rubin in the quarter-finals. 
