<HEADLINE> Cholera Affects Tanzania's Exports of Fish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Due to an outbreak of
cholera in east Africa, the European Union (EU) has imposed a ban
on the exports of fresh fish fillets from northern Tanzania's
Mwanza Region skirting the Lake Victoria.
</P>
<P>
Frozen fish fillets, however, have not been banned, The
Guardian today quoted an official with the Lake Victoria Fish
Processing Industries Association as saying.
</P>
<P>
The official, who requested anonymity, said in Mwanza on
Monday that the ban would affect all fishing industries by 50
percent.
</P>
<P>
"Fifty percent of our products are fresh fish fillets which
have a reliable market in the world and the remaining half are
frozen fish fillets which do not attract customers," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The ban, though temporarily imposed, will hurt greatly the
economy in areas around Lake Victoria, the world's second-largest
freshwater lake. 
</P>
