<HEADLINE> Cuba Elects New National, Provincial Assemblies Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The Cubans have elected 601
deputies to the National Assembly of People's Power and 1,192
representatives for the 14 provincial assemblies, the National
Electoral Commission said Monday.
</P>
<P>
As many as 7.93 million Cubans, or 98.35 percent of the
eligible voters, voted in the Sunday's national and
provincial assemblies elections.
</P>
<P>
President Fidel Castro, for the fifth time, was elected deputy
to the national assembly.
</P>
<P>
According to the Cuban constitution, 45 days after the congress
election, the 601 deputies-elect will select members for the Council
of State and Council of Ministers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
