<HEADLINE> Flamingoes Increase in Kenya's Lake of Nakuru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Unofficial data from the
bi-annual African water fowl census launched at central Kenya's
Lake Nakuru National Park on Sunday indicated a rapid increase in
the flamingo population over last year.
</P>
<P>
Although the results are not yet out, participants in the
count said the flamingoes numbered more than one million, the
Daily Nation newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
Only about 5,000 flamingoes had been left at the lake last
year after a severe water recession as a result of drought. But
the lake's water level has been rising due to the current heavy
rains.
</P>
<P>
The birds then had migrated to lakes Bogoria and Elmentaita
while some flocks had flown to northern Lake Turkana.
</P>
<P>
All these are alkaline lakes located in the Rift Valley, the
habitat of the fowl that has a large red bill and coral-red outer
wing coverts.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the flamingoes, pelicans and Egyptian geese have
also returned to Lake Nakuru in large numbers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980113.0257 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangzhou to Build New International Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, will start the construction of a new
international airport later this year.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Lin Shusen said Monday at a news conference that the
city would ensure that the airport's first phase would be ready
for service in 2001, in time for the Ninth National Games.
</P>
<P>
Baiyun International Airport, located inside the city proper,
is one of the busiest airports in China. To cater to demands of
aviation transport, construction of a new airport in suburban
Guangzhou was proposed and approved by the State Council and the
Central Military Commission in July of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The new airport will sit at the juncture of Renhe Town of the
Baiyun District and Xinhua Town of Huadu City. It will cover an
area of 1,453 hectares and will have three runways. When
completed, the new airport will be able to handle 80 million
passengers and 2.5 million tons of cargo a year.
</P>
<P>
In the first phase, two runways will be finished. When the
first phase is completed, the airport will be able to handle 27
million passengers a year.
</P>
<P>
The new airport will cost 20 billion yuan. An airport company
will be established with shareholders from the Civil Aviation
Administration of China (CAAC), Guangdong Province and Guangzhou
City. The company will be responsible for 35 percent, or 5.2
billion yuan, of the total investment. The remaining investment
will come from CAAC, Guangdong Province, Guangzhou City and China
Southern Airlines.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Lin said that the city is also looking for overseas
loans for the new airport's construction, in addition to several
state financial organizations which have shown strong interest
in financing the project.
</P>
<P>
According to Lin, more than 20,000 people from 6,000 rural
families in nine villages will have to relocate. Buildings
covering a combined floor space of more than 1 million square
meters are being torn down and relocated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
