<HEADLINE> New Commission Established to Propose New Bosnian Flag </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, January 12 (Xinhua) -- An independent commission was
established on Monday to propose the new look of the Bosnian flag
by the end of January.
</P>
<P>
The commission was set up by the International High
Representative for Bosnia-Herzegovina, the Sarajevo-based office
of Carlos Westerdorp said Monday in a statement issued in Sarajevo.
</P>
<P>
Seven Bosnian intellectuals were appointed as members of the
commission. At their first informal meeting they agreed the
proposal for a new flag should be drafted by January 30.
</P>
<P>
The appearance of the flag is an issue representatives of
Bosnia's three peoples have as yet failed to agree on. 
