in Melbourne on Wednesday, his first match since tearing his left
calf muscle during the Davis Cup final against Sweden last
November.
</P>
<P>
With 10 Grand Slam titles to his credit, Sampras took the
Colonial Classic as preparation for the Australian Open to chase
to beat the record of 12 titles claimed by Roy Emerson and the
record of 11 held by both Bjorn Borg and Rod Laver.
</P>
<P>
The round-robin format splits the eight players into two group,
with Sampras lined up with Gustavo Kuerten, Mark Philippoussis and
Greg Rusedski. The other group features defending champion Michael
Chang, Thomas Muster, Andre Agassi and Goran Ivanisevic. 
