<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Receive Loan From ADB </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will receive an 80
million U.S. dollar concessional loan from the Asian Development
Bank (ADB) for capital market development program (CMDP) under an
agreement signed between Bangladesh and the ADB in Manila on
Monday, local press reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The loan will come from the ADB's concessional lending window,
the Asian Development Fund, for the CMDP which will be implemented
over three years under the Finance Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The program will create a capital market and help establish the
institutional infrastructure necessary to sustain its long-term
development, the reports said, the ADB will also provide a
technical assistance grant of 2.04 million dollars for the
governance and capacity building requirements of the key
institutions involved in the program.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Bangladesh will also receive 310 million taka (about
6.9 million dollars) as grant from Canada for implementation of
another development project under a memorandum of understanding
signed between the two countries in Dhaka on Monday, the reports
said.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the project funded by Canada is to enhance net
return to farmers from agricultural production through diversified
production system and marketing alternative.  
</P>
</TEXT>
