<HEADLINE> NZ Banks Raise Lending Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wellington, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The ASB Bank has become the
latest New Zealand money lender to put up its floating mortgage
rates.
</P>
<P>
The bank announced Tuesday that it has raised its floating
mortgage rate by half a percentage point to 10.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The decision followed similar moves taken Tuesday by the
ANZ-Post Bank and the Countrywide Bank.
</P>
<P>
Last week, Bank of New Zealand, the Citibank and the Hong Kong
Bank also increased their lending rates to around 10.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The rise is related to the recent fall in the value of the New
Zealand dollar, which pushed up wholesale interest rates.
</P>
