<HEADLINE> Kalinic Re-elected Bosnian Serb Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Dragan Kalinic of the Serb
Democratic Party was re-elected speaker of the Republika Srpska
assembly at the second session of the newly-elected regional
parliament held in Bijeljina Monday, Yugoslavia's Tanjug news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav news agency said Nikola Poplasen of the Serb
Radical Party and Jovan Mitrovic of the Serb National Alliance
were elected deputy speakers. Momir Malic from the Serbian
Socialist Party was elected secretary-general of the assembly.
</P>
<P>
The Bosnian Serb assembly, which emerged from the November 22
and 23 elections, met in Bijeljina Monday in a renewed bid to
reach agreement on new parliament officials.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Westendorp, top civilian international official in
Bosnia, and ambassadors representing the five-nation Contact Group
on Bosnia, were attending the session along with Bosnian Serb
President Biljana Plavsic and Momcilo Krajisnik, Serb member of
Bosnian tripartite presidency.
</P>
<P>
At the inaugural session of the assembly on December 27, the
Serb Democratic Party and its ally the Serb Radical Party refused
to share power with Plavsic's Serb National Alliance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
