<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shift in Preference to Semi-luxury cars in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 13 (Xinhua)-- Even as the automobile
industry in India faces a sharp slowdown reflective of the overall
economic situation, there is a discernible shift in consumer
preferences from economy cars to semi-luxury ones in the country,
said a survey here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This trend comes at a time when several global players and
domestic majors are expected to hit the road with semi-luxury cars
this year.
</P>
<P>
A quick look at the sales data for the first eight months of
the current fiscal year (April 1, 1997-March 31, 1998) has shown
that while economy segment car sales went up by 4.9 percent,
semi-luxury cars showed a massive 58.79 percent growth.
</P>
<P>
Keen observers of the automobile sector believe that the
semi-luxury cars would be attracting most attention at the Auto
Expo '98 scheduled from January 15 to 21 this year. The exhibition
will display an unprecedented presentation from almost all the
world's top automobile manufacturers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
