<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The following are economic
news briefs from Latin American countries:
</P>
<P>
Chile Closes 1997 With Big Reserves
</P>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- International monetary reserves of Chile reached
17.84 billion dollars by the end of 1997, four times as much as
the previous year.
</P>
<P>
25,000 Retail Businesses Close In Argentina
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Argentina's Federation of Chambers and
Commercial Centers (known as Fedecamaras) said more than 25,000
retail businesses were closed during 1997 nationwide.
</P>
<P>
Fedecamaras said the main cause for the closures was the new
trading patterns imposed by modern supermarkets.
</P>
<P>
Panamanian Power Companies For Sale
</P>
<P>
PANAMA CITY -- Public auctions of Panamanian power companies
will be held in June, said the Director of Hydraulic Resources and
Power Supply (HRPS), Fernando Aramburu Porras.
</P>
<P>
He said future owners of the companies would decide whether to
retain the same numbers of workers.
</P>
<P>
Uruguayan Spending on Culture in 1997
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- Culture consumption in Uruguay reached 408
million dollars during 1997, according to a study carried out by a
publishing house.
</P>
<P>
Uruguayans spent 122 million dollars on music equipment, TV
sets, VCR`S and computers.
</P>
<P>
Other outstanding aspects of consumption were dailies and
magazines which made up 70 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
People also spent 52 million dollars on books, 36 million
dollars on payments for cable TV and 28 million dollars to attend
concerts and art performances, the study said. 
</P>
