<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Lazio's veteran Roberto Mancini
was named the top Italian serie A soccer player of 1997 on Monday,
while defending champion Juventus of Turin swept the other five
awards.
</P>
<P>
A total of 320 players from Italy's first division soccer
league casted their votes for the awards.
</P>
<P>
Mancini, who scored 144 goals over 17 seasons, tallied 15 in 33
games in the 1996-97 campaign with Sampdoria of Genoa. He moved to
Lazio of Rome from Sampodria last Summer.
</P>
<P>
Juventus, which won its record 24th league title and made it to
the Champions Cup final last seaon, was selected as the top club.
</P>
<P>
Other awards were all to the premier club with best foreigner
for French playmaker Zinedine Zidane, best coach for Marcillo
Lippi, best goalkeeper for Angelo Peruzzi and best young player
for Filippo Inzaghi.
</P>
<P>
Inzaghi and Zidane were also the nominees for the top player
honor while the other finalists for best foreigner were French
defender Lilian Thuram of AC Parma and Argetine midfielder
Sebastian Veron of Sampdoria. 
