affairs department has decided to install video cameras in the
pitches to prevent violence in soccer competitions.
</P>
<P>
As soccer violences become rampant in the country, the
Argentine government has recently directed its Internal Affairs
department to take the responsibility of ensuring safety and
security in the sport.
</P>
<P>
With video cameras installed around the pitches, more policemen
were also dispatched there to ensure the flows of onlookers and to
arrest the troublemakers once violences erupt in the stadiums, the
Internal Affairs said.
</P>
<P>
Police authorities can even monitor the situation through video
cameras and dig out those troublemakers to ensure the security for
both players and audience.
</P>
<P>
The Internal Affairs was also enpowered to close down those
sports organizations who were caught of negligence and seeking
support of trouble-making fans by giving free tickets.
</P>
<P>
In December, one soccer fan was shot to death, with other eight
wounded in a national league match, fueling the cry for more
measures to be taken to ensure the safety of both players and fans
througout the country. 
