<HEADLINE> Taiwan Boosts Investment In Neighboring Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Direct shipments between Taiwan
and neighboring Fujian province increased in consecutive months
last year since the service began in April.
</P>
<P>
According to the International Business Daily sponsored by the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC), 11
ships carried 327 shipments of goods between the two sides of the
Taiwan Straits from April to November. The total shipment volume
equaled 73,600 standard containers.
</P>
<P>
In the first 11 months of 1997, Taiwan increased its investment
in Fujian by 90 percent and received 57 percent more imports from
the province over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan pumped 1.169 billion U.S. dollars into Fujian and had
290 million U.S. dollars in imports from the province during
January to November, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan has become one of the major sources of overseas
investment for Fujian, with 4,987 projects involving 9.523 billion
U.S. dollars in the province by last November. More than 5.5
billion U.S. dollars have already been invested in the projects.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural projects and ventures involving hundreds of
millions of US dollars are major components of Taiwan investment
in Fujian. Agricultural joint venture zones in Zhangzhou and
Fuzhou cities in Fujian has attracted over 600 cooperative
projects from Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Fujian has set up four investment zones for Taiwan and gave
priority to Taiwan investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
