<HEADLINE> Technicians Develop Facility for Making Automotive Pistons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese technicians have
developed a facility for making pistons, a major engine part, for
300,000 Santana cars to be produced annually in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The piston research program has been listed as one of major
state science-and-technology projects from 1996 to 2000 and has
passed a state-level appraisal.
</P>
<P>
So far, 70 percent of key facilities for car-making have been
introduced from foreign countries and China has been relying on
foreign facilities for making pistons.
</P>
<P>
The piston program was jointly launched by Shanghai Jiaotong
University and Shanghai Piston Factory.
</P>
<P>
With the development of the piston-making facility, China can
save 5.59 million Deutsche marks for introduction of the same sort
of facility and 32 million yuan (4 million U.S. dollars) for
technical upgrades to the facility.
</P>
<P>
China's car industry has grown rapidly and the country's annual
capacity for producing motor vehicles is expected to reach 3
million soon. The Sino-German Shanghai Volkswagen Corp. plans to
produce 500,000 Santana cars annually by the end of this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
