<HEADLINE> Conference On Energy To Be Held In Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The 3rd Hemispheric Meeting of
Energy Ministers will be held January 15 and 16 in Caracas, the
Minister of Energy and Mines, Erwin Arrieta, announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
Arrieta said that the meeting comes in the wake of new concern
about free market, quality of development and preservation of the
environment in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelan official said that participating countries will
issue a document to spread the achievments made by American
countries on energy cooperation.
</P>
<P>
A source of the Venezuelan Energy Ministry indicated that the
3rd hemispheric meeting will conclude with the singning of the
"Caracas Declaration On Energy" which will include a plan of
action to equilibrate the supply and demand of fuels.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is in line with the needs of social and economic
development of the continent to enter globalization and face
challenges through dialogue and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The conference will be attended by Energy ministers from United
States, Guatemala, Mexico, Colombia, Peru, Dominican Republic,
Brazil, Argentina, Trinidad &AMP; Tobago, Ecuador, Saint Kitts,
Uruguay, Chile, Bolivia, Costa Rica, Canada and Paraguay. 
</P>
