<HEADLINE> Brazil Tax Collection Increases in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Tax collection in Brazil
amounted to 112,600 dollars in 1997, up 18.5 percent over the
previous year, Federal Income Minister Everardo Maciel said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Maciel said the hike was mainly due to the increment of 13
percent of the import tax, which was applied mostly to purchases
of manufactured products and vehicles abroad.
</P>
<P>
Another positive factor was the "26 percent expansion on taxes
for money remittance from abroad" especially those applied to
financial gains gotten overseas during the last quarter of 1997.
</P>
</TEXT>
