<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade In Southeast China Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Foreign trade in east China's
Fujian Province was worth an estimated 19.5 billion US dollars in
1997, up 16.4 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
This consisted of 11.5 billion US dollars in exports and eight
billion US dollars in imports, up 15 and 19 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Fujian approved 2,298 new foreign-funded projects last year, up
15.6 percent from 1996, and overseas investment involved totaled
4.5 billion US dollars, down 30.5 percent. The actual investment
used was up 2.9 percent to nearly 4.2 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the first 11 months of 1997, Fujian signed 2,487 new
agreements for overseas labor cooperation, up 11.9 percent. By the
end of November, 53,400 people from Fujian were working overseas,
the largest number among all Chinese provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
Trade cooperation between Fujian and Taiwan increased in 1997
by two percent to 2.6 billion US dollars, and Fujian approved
5,044 projects funded by Taiwanese investors, amounting to 9.6
billion US dollars, with actual investment of 5.9 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Fujian expects exports this year to be worth 13 billion US
dollars, up 13 percent from last year, and actual overseas
investment is expected to remain the same as for 1997, at four
billion US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
