<HEADLINE> Quake Strikes Chile, No Victims Reported </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, January 12 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake occurred Monday
in Central Chile and there have been no reports of victims or
damage.
</P>
<P>
The shaking, with a magnitud of 6.3 degrees on Richter scale,
was registered at 7:15 local time and its epicenter was located
some 70 kms from the city of Tongoy, in the Fourth Region, said
the Interior Ministry`s National Bureau of Emergency.
</P>
<P>
The quake was strongly felt in the cities of La Serena and the
capital Santiago.
</P>
<P>
The Department of Sysmology at the University of Chile reported
the phenomenon was superficial, five kilometers deep and was
followed by lower-powered imperceptible tremors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
