<DOCNO> XIE19980113.0315 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine House Passes New Oil Deregulation Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine House of
Representatives Monday passed a new oil deregulation bill on the
third and final reading, paving the way for a quick congressional
passage of the vital oil bill.
</P>
<P>
A bicameral committee, composed of representatives from both
the House and the Senate, is expected to begin talks Tuesday night
to come up with a final congressional version of the oil bill.
</P>
<P>
The Senate approved its own bill on the oil industry's
deregulation last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The House' approval of the new oil bill came at the end of a
four-day special session of the Congress, which was called by
President Fidel Ramos to tackle the bill to enable the country's
exit from the control of the International Monetary Fund (IMF).
</P>
<P>
The old oil deregulation law, which took effect in February
1997, was nullified by the Supreme Court last November on the
ground that the law violated the constitution and the rule of free
trade.
</P>
<P>
The old law provided for a 7 percent tariff for refined
petroleum products, and a 3 percent tariff for crude oil, to
encourage firms to invest in the domestic refinery industry.
</P>
<P>
But the Supreme Court ruled that free trade would be hindered
if oil firms were forced to choose between investing huge amounts
in refineries and paying higher tariffs.
</P>
<P>
The abolishment of the old oil deregulation law prevented the
country from getting free from the decades of economic supervision
by the IMF before the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Under the new oil bill adopted by the House, a uniform 3
percent tariff will be imposed on both finished oil products and
crude oil.
</P>
<P>
The bill also provides a six-month transition period before the
full deregulation of the country's oil industry. During the
period, oil companies are barred from jacking up prices of
"socially sensitive" products like kerosene and diesel.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980113.0316 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
