<HEADLINE> Colombian Inmates Take Hostages 560 People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Inmates at the San
Isidro Jail in the city of Popayan are holding hostages 560
visitors in protest against living conditions at the prison,
authorities informed on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The hostages, most of them are women, will not be freed until
representatives of the People's Attorney and the representation of
Popayan come to negotiate with the convicted, representatives
of the mutineers have reportedly said.
</P>
<P>
Jail's Manager Sandra Vazquez said that the uprising is taking
place in all the sections of the prison of the Cauca Department's
capital.
</P>
<P>
She said the situation is "stable" but reinforcements are
coming from the police.
</P>
<P>
Requests from inmates include the setting up of a telephone
line in each section, the supply of drinking water and enough beds
to meet inmates' needs and the improvement of health services.
</P>
<P>
Vazquez said the prison has a full capacity for 900 beds but
the number of prisoners surpasses the thousand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
