<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuela`s Foreign Debt To Rise This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Payment of Venezuela's foreign
debt will be 71.24 higher this year than those in 1997 and payment
of interests of the same debt will go up 10.84 percent, said
Monday authorities from the Finance Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela`s foreign debt services will reach this fiscal year
4.36 billion dollars, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The amount accounts for 18.48 percent of the budgetary expenses
of the country and 2.44 billion dollars are capital and 1.92
billion are due to interests.
</P>
<P>
The total external public debt of the country will amount for
the fiscal year to 22.21 billion dollars. 
</P>
