<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ronaldo Wins FIFA Player of Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian soccer star Ronaldo was
named FIFA's Player of the Year for the second time in a row by a
majority of votes in Marne La Vallee, France on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"I feel very honored to win this award, this distinction, at
such a young age," said the 21-year-old Ronaldo.
</P>
<P>
Over the past years, Ronaldo has helped his teams win the
Spanish Cup, the Netherlands Cup and the Copa America.
</P>
<P>
And Ronaldo, after winning the coveted honor, was still in the
mood for more trophies, especially the World Cup in France, saying
"as long as I have motivation I will still go on and want to win
more and more."
</P>
<P>
He is surely to spearhead Brazil this summer for his debut
World Cup as he was too young to compete in 1994 where he was an
unused substitute at 17.
</P>
<P>
The golden trophy was presented by Pele and FIFA president Joao
Havelange at a banquet with Ronaldo attending with his mother and
father.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo scored 480 points with 86 first-place votes from the
121 possible, his Brazilian teammate Roberto Carlos, who plays for
Real Madrid was a distant second with 65 votes, just ahead of
Dutchman Dennis Bergkamp of Arsenal, and Frenchman Zinedine
Zidane, who plays for Juventus Turin. Bergkamp and Zidane scored
62 points.
</P>
<P>
National team coaches from 121 countries voted for the title.
Last year was closer, Ronaldo had 329 to Liberian George Weah,
second with 140.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo became the first two-time winner of the world award,
which has only been given since 1991. Previous winners were
Lothar Matthaus of Germany, Marco van Basten of Netherlands,
Roberto Baggio of Italy, Romario of Brazil and Weah before Ronaldo
won for 1996.
</P>
<P>
Last month, he was named the European player of the season.
</P>
<P>
The only thing left for Ronaldo is to help his Brazilian team
win the World Cup in France starting in June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
