<HEADLINE> Hawks Guard Smith Named NBA Player of Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Atlanta Hawks guard Steve
Smith was named NBA Player of the Week on Monday for his average
26.3 points and leading role for Hawks' 3-0 record.
</P>
<P>
Smith shot 52 percent (24-of-42) from the field and averaged
4.7 assists and 4.3 rebounds per game. He began the week with a
season-high 35 points in a 106-86 win at Golden State last
Wednesday and scored 22 points in each of the next two games.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for the award were Boston Celtics forward
Antoine Walker, who scored a career-high 49 points in a loss at
Washington last Wednesday, Los Angeles Lakers center Shaquille
O'Neal and Washington Wizards forward Chris Webber. 
