<HEADLINE> European Shares Down on Asian Turmoil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Major stock markets in Europe,
undermined by the continuing turmoil in Asian markets, sharply
downed Monday and all ended with big losses.
</P>
<P>
Britain's FTSE 100 index was at its worst level falling by
almost three percent and the market saw 26 billion pounds (42
billion U.S. dollars) wiped from the value of its shares as Asian
flu took hold again.
</P>
<P>
But the market clambered back from session lows as Wall Street
staged a recovery from fierce early losses, with the index ending
at 5,068.8, down 69.5 points or 1.35 percent.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that markets were still fragile in the wake of
deepening Asian economic woes.
</P>
<P>
The DAX-30 index in Frankfurt had been more than four percent
lower earlier today before closing at 4,087.28, down 149.66 points
or 3.53 percent.
</P>
<P>
The market was in a "tailspin" because of the heavy losses in
Asia, one dealer said.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, the CAC-30 index suffered its fifth consecutive
session of losses, as nervous investors dumped stocks after the
latest relapse on Asian bourses.
</P>
<P>
But the index managed to bounce off lows to close down 57.27 at
2,862.54 points.  
</P>
</TEXT>
