<HEADLINE> Britain Calls on U.S. to Take More Flexible </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 12 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook, who is due to hold talks with American Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright Thursday, will call on the U.S. government to
adopt a more flexible approach towards Iran, a government official
said here today.
</P>
<P>
The official told reporters that Cook will stress that
Washington and the European Union (EU) need new policies to take
advantage of the more conciliatory Iranian approach.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Iranian President Mohammad Khatami said
last week that contacts between academics, writers, journalists
and tourists could help improve the bilateral relations with the
United States after two decades of hostility between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The official said: "In the British view, unilateral U.S.
sanctions (against Iran) will not work. We need to devise new ways
of engaging this important country at a critical time."
</P>
<P>
"Like the U.S. administration, we believe it's right to try to
capitalize on the new tone. We must try to encourage Iranian
moderates," the official said.
</P>
<P>
However, the official said that there could be no question of
relaxing rules designed to prevent Iran from acquiring weapons of
mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
"We need tough policies to counter Iranian efforts to acquire
weapons of mass destruction," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
