<HEADLINE> Rybkin on Russian-Chechen Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The main achievement made by the
Russian Security Council was establishment of peace in Chechnya
and adoption of a concept of national security, Head of the
Russian Security Council Ivan Rybkin said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with members of the international Committee
"Conference of the Den Bourg Fund" Rybkin said the best preventive
measure as regards Chechnya was the implementation of an economic
agreement signed on May 12, 1997, and around 40 other agreements
concluded by Russian ministries and departments with Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
He meanwhile noted the Russian government was not doing enough
for the realization of these agreements.
</P>
<P>
Russian Vice Premier Ramazan Abdulatipov visited last Saturday
to Grozny, capital of the break-way republic, that made the first
step towards realization of these agreements, Rybkin was quoted as
reporting.
</P>
<P>
In Rybkin's opinion, a legal basis for relations between Moscow
and Grozny already exists and now, concrete ways should be found
for realization of this basis.
</P>
<P>
The International Consultative Committee incorporates
representatives of state, public, religious structures of Russia,
the United States, Great Britain, the Netherlands and the
Conference of European Churches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
