<HEADLINE> Greek Vegetable Markets Close in Protest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Greece's fruit and vegetable
producers today closed down all the open air vegetable markets
throughout the country in protest against an increase in their
annual sum taxation payment.
</P>
<P>
About 10,000 producers in Athens and 28,000 in other parts of
the country also urged the Greek government to withdraw the
ceiling for the prices of fruit and vegetables, and not to issue
licenses to hawkers.
</P>
<P>
The producers' annual sum taxation payment reportedly increased
from 120,000 drachmas (about 419.6 U.S. dollars) to 180,000
drachmas (about 629.4 dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
