<HEADLINE> WCIT To Be Held In Virginia,U.S.A. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 12 (Xinhua) -- 1998 World Congress on
Information Technology(WCIT) will be held in Virginia, the United
States of America, from June 21 to 24.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference here today, Dr. George Newstrom, Chairman
of Board of Directors of the congress, said that more than 1700
international technology and business leaders from 50 countries or
regions will take part in the congress.
</P>
<P>
"The WCIT will address the challenges of creating and marketing
technology that consumers need and want", he said.
</P>
<P>
The attendees will look at issues related to how the
convergence of information technology in meeting consumers' demand
today and in the future.
</P>
<P>
The WCIT, which has a history of 20 years, meet every two years
in cities and regions around the world, but this is the first time
that it is to be held in a university of the United States--the
George Mason University, Virginia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
